This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically crowd counting, and proposes a new method for incorporating side information into deep learning models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of adaptive weights, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new dataset, which involves data collection and annotation, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the potential application of the proposed method to other computer vision tasks, such as image deconvolution, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
